# CI/CD is non-blocking by default

After a push/PR, **do not sit idle watching CI** (a run is ≈8–15 min). Local `npm run presubmit`
is the gate before push; CI is the safety net. Default flow: **fire-and-forget + fix on failure.**
Canonical: [`docs/PR_WORKFLOW.md`](../../docs/PR_WORKFLOW.md) § CI without blocking the session.

## Default after push (do this, then move on)

1. **Arm auto-merge** so green merges itself with no agent action:
   `gh pr merge <n> --auto --squash --delete-branch` (success path needs nobody).
2. **Background-watch for failure only** — start a backgrounded Shell job:
   `npm run ci:watch -- <n>` with `block_until_ms: 0` and `notify_on_output` pattern
   `^CI_WATCH: (FAIL|TIMEOUT|ERROR)` (reason: "CI failed"). It stays silent while pending and
   prints one sentinel (`CI_WATCH: PASS|FAIL|TIMEOUT|NO_CHECKS`) at the end.
   For **direct `main` pushes** (no PR): `npm run ci:watch -- main` or pass the workflow run id.
3. **Immediately continue** the next unit of work. Do not `AwaitShell` the watcher and do not
   re-poll CI in chat. The completion/failure notification will reach you between turns.

## On a failure notification

- Resolve root cause: `npm run report:ci-failure -- <run-id>` (run id is in the FAIL sentinel).
- Fix **within the PR's scope** (never weaken CI, never `--no-verify`). Re-run the relevant local
  check, push again — auto-merge re-arms automatically. Restart `ci:watch` for the new commit.
- If the failure looks unrelated/flaky, merge latest `main` first and re-check before "fixing"
  (see [`docs/FLAKY_TESTS.md`](../../docs/FLAKY_TESTS.md), [`docs/CI_RELIABILITY.md`](../../docs/CI_RELIABILITY.md)).

## When to block instead (foreground babysit)

Only watch synchronously when the user asked to **merge now / babysit**, it's a **hotfix for broken
`main`**, or it's the **last action of the session** and nothing else is queued. Use skill
`labs-babysit-pr`.

## Honest limits (state these, don't pretend otherwise)

- Backgrounded shells are **session-scoped**: if the session ends, the watcher stops. **Auto-merge
  still covers the success case** without you. A failure after the session ends stays a red open PR,
  caught next session (`gh pr list`) or by the Nightly detector — call this out when you hand off.
- Never report a PR as "merged/green" you did not observe. Say "pushed; auto-merge armed; watching
  in background" and let the notification confirm.

Root cause class: `ci-blocking-idle` — agent burned session time waiting on CI instead of
backgrounding it. See [`docs/CONTINUOUS_PROCESS_IMPROVEMENT.md`](../../docs/CONTINUOUS_PROCESS_IMPROVEMENT.md).
